.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB--color\fR \fIWHEN\fR
Controls colored output. Default: auto. Possible values: auto, always, never.
.TP
\fB--quiet\fR
Suppress progress indicators and non\-essential labels.
.TP
\fB--profile\fR \fINAME\fR
Profile name to load from .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB--settings\-file\fR \fIPATH\fR
Explicit settings file path; defaults to upward search for .hpc\-compose/settings.toml.
.TP
\fB-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help (see a summary with '\-h').
.TP
\fB-V\fR, \fB--version\fR
Print version.
.SH FILES
.TP
\fBcompose.yaml\fR
Fallback compose specification file when \-f or \-\-file is omitted and the active context does not provide one.
.TP
\fB<compose\-file\-dir>/hpc\-compose.sbatch\fR
Default rendered batch script path written by up or run when \-\-script\-out is not set.
.TP
\fB<submit\-dir>/.hpc\-compose/\fR
Default runtime root: tracked job metadata plus per\-job logs, metrics, state.json, and artifact state under <job\-id>/. Resolved to an absolute path at submit time and overridable with x\-slurm.runtime_root.
.TP
\fB~/.cache/hpc\-compose\fR
Default cache root for imported and prepared image artifacts when x\-slurm.cache_dir is unset.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
\fBHOME\fR
Used to resolve the default cache path and default configuration locations.
.TP
\fBPATH\fR
Used to resolve external commands such as enroot, sbatch, srun, squeue, sacct, sstat, and scancel.
.TP
\fBENROOT_CONFIG_PATH\fR
Consulted during preflight when checking Enroot configuration discovery.
.TP
\fBXDG_CONFIG_HOME\fR
Consulted during preflight when checking Enroot configuration discovery.
.TP
\fBSLURM_SUBMIT_DIR\fR
Fallback base for the tracked runtime directory in dry\-run previews; real submissions bake the resolved absolute runtime root into the script.
.TP
\fBSLURM_JOB_ID\fR
Used in tracked runtime paths and in artifact export directory expansion after submission.
.TP
\fBHPC_COMPOSE_PRIMARY_NODE and related HPC_COMPOSE_* runtime variables\fR
Injected into services inside submitted jobs to describe allocation metadata and resume state.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
\fB0\fR
The command completed successfully.
.TP
\fB1\fR
A generic failure with no more specific category: an unexpected error, local I/O, or an external tool reporting an error.
.TP
\fB2\fR
A usage error (an invalid flag or argument combination) or an invalid spec. clap also exits 2 for parse\-level usage errors such as an unknown flag or a missing argument.
.TP
\fB3\fR
A preflight or environment\-readiness failure, including an unreachable cluster. Emitted by preflight, doctor, and the reachability checks in up \-\-remote and the remote follow\-up commands.
.TP
\fB4\fR
Lint findings are present and failed the configured gate. Pass lint \-\-allow\-warnings to treat warning\-level findings as advisory.
.TP
\fBchild status\fR
For direct\-execution commands (run, alloc, shell, notebook, reach, exec) the executed child process's exit status is propagated verbatim, so scripts and CI can distinguish, for example, a test runner's exit code 2 from 5. A propagated status may coincide with a reserved code above.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
hpc\-compose up \-f compose.yaml
hpc\-compose when \-f compose.yaml \-\-partition gpu8 \-\-free\-nodes 4
hpc\-compose plan \-f compose.yaml
hpc\-compose evolve \-\-output compose.yaml
hpc\-compose debug \-f compose.yaml \-\-preflight
hpc\-compose validate \-f compose.yaml
hpc\-compose inspect \-\-verbose \-f compose.yaml
hpc\-compose config \-f compose.yaml
hpc\-compose preflight \-f compose.yaml
.fi
